# Root environment contract example (no real secrets in git).
#
# Load order:
#   1) .env.shared
#   2) services/<service>/.env
#   3) deployment/runtime overrides
#
# Shared file (.env.shared) must contain only shared infrastructure/runtime defaults,
# e.g. Redis, RabbitMQ, common logging, shared profile values.
#
# Service file (services/<service>/.env) must contain only service-owned settings,
# e.g. DB host/name/user/password, service ports, service-specific secrets/URLs.
#
# Keep this root file as documentation-only. Put executable values in:
#   - .env.shared (shared)
#   - services/<service>/.env (service-owned)